DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The equation 
\[x^2-8x+y^2-6y -50=0\]
defines a circle with center
\((\)  \{ ans_rule(4) \} \(,\)
EOT
ANS(num_cmp("4"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\{ ans_rule(4) \} \()\) and radius
EOT
ANS(num_cmp("3"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\{ ans_rule(4) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp("sqrt(75)"));


TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR Hint: 
Complete the square in \(x\) and in \(y\).
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
Completing the squares gives: \(x^2-8x+y^2-6y -50= (x-4)^2 + (y-3)^2
-75 = 0\) which can be rewritten as \( (x-4)^2 + (y-3)^2 =75\), the
standard equation of a circle with radius \(\sqrt{75}\) centered at
\((4,3)\).
EOT







